===Did not play=== Of these players, all played against Sweden, except for Bobby Orr.<ref>{{cite news |newspaper=The Globe and Mail |title=Crude Team Canada ties sneaky Sweden 4–4 |date=September 18, 1972 |page=S01}}</ref> Dionne, Glennie and Tallon played against Czechoslovakia.{{sfn|Podnieks|2012|p=231}} * [[Brian Glennie]] (#38), [[Jocelyn Guevremont]] (#37), [[Bobby Orr]] (#4), [[Dale Tallon]] (#32) – defence * [[Marcel Dionne]] (#34), [[Rick Martin (ice hockey)|Rick Martin]] (#36) – forward * [[Eddie Johnston]] (#1) – goaltender
Jersey numbers: ''The Globe and Mail''<ref name="gmjerseyno">{{cite news |newspaper=The Globe and Mail |date=September 4, 1972 |page=S06 |title=Canada-Russia teams}}</ref>
Three junior-age players were invited to training camp to take part in practices. All three had been drafted in the [[1972 NHL Entry Draft]] and were clients of Alan Eagleson. The three stayed with the team during the Canadian stage of the series. * [[Billy Harris (ice hockey b. 1952)|Billy Harris]] (#39), [[Michel Larocque (ice hockey b. 1952)|Michel Larocque]] (#30){{sfn|Bendell|2012|p=107}} and [[John Van Boxmeer]] (#40).{{sfn|Podnieks|2012|p=24}}
====Coaches==== * [[Harry Sinden]] – coach * [[John Ferguson, Sr.|John Ferguson]] – assistant
