The '''United Press International Athlete of the Year Award''' was conferred annually between [[1974 in sports|1974]] and [[1995 in sports|1995]], one each to the individuals adjudged, without restriction to nationality or [[sport]] contested, to be the [[male]] and [[female]] ''[[sportsperson|athlete]] of the year'' by a panel of [[sportswriter]]s and [[newspaper editor|editors]] constituted under the auspices of the [[United Press International]].<ref>In [[1974 in sports|1974]] and [[1975 in sports|1975]], the [[voting]] panel comprised [[sportswriter]]s and [[newspaper editor|editor]]s exclusively from [[Europe]].</ref>
